The paper also discusses the theoretical and computational aspects of the two techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of time integrators, which could place it in the sub-categories cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) or cs.MS (Mathematical Software). Finally, the paper discusses error bounds and simulation time, which could place it in the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
